I started my project by launching the VPC and More feature, creating one AZ, one Public Subnet, no Private Subnet, and updating the route tables

The CIDR blocks for VPCs 1 and 2 are 10.1.0.0/16 and 10.2.0.0/16, respectively. They have to be unique to ensure the IP addresses of the two VPCs don't overlap. An overlapping IP address will cause connection issues and routing conflicts.

