## Updating route tables

After accepting a peering connection, my VPCs' route tables need to be updated because, despite being accepted, it still doesn't know whose IP address is accepted. Updating the routes sends the right traffic to the right address

My VPCs' new routes have a destination of 10.2.0.0/16 for route table 1 and 10.1.0.0/16 for route table 2. The routes' target was the peering connection 

